{"tid":1815264,"cid":20,"subCid":0,"title":"SONY出私家車","createTime":"2020-01-07T11:29:45.000Z","updateTime":"2020-01-10T16:27:09.000Z","uid":126833,"like":9,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":34,"replies":[{"pid":"5c365d5c923d7eed2a0eabd4a0369bb03479e59a","tid":1815264,"uid":126833,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-07T11:29:45.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/Ajv2RSu.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FAjv2RSu.jpg&h=145b7cdc&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/oAWxuEa.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FoAWxuEa.jpg&h=7bca6fad&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nSony has debuted its first-ever car - or at least a prototype sturdy enough to drive to center stage - replete with sensors for safety and a panoramic dashboard screen for mobile entertainment. <br />\n<br />\nThe so-called Vision S was the highlight from left field during Sony's otherwise underwhelming Monday night keynote presentation at the Consumer Electronics Show (CES) in Las Vegas. <br />\n<br />\nIts announcement followed the unveiling of the logo for the PlayStation 5, but not the much-anticipated gaming system hardware as well as a broadly-brushed recap of the company's sensor, camera and safety products. <br />\n<br />\nSony hinted that the Vision S prototype is designed to be an 'EV,' or electric vehicle, and highlighted its 'adaptability' and continuous cloud updating capabilities. <br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-7859107/Sony-rolls-electric-car-prototype-CES.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fsciencetech%2Farticle-7859107%2FSony-rolls-electric-car-prototype-CES.html&d=rLp99s1CaA%2FTm5LA4NL6TQHlXPv3B7QU%2BsV1%2BUkEKpk%3D&h=1837a729\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-7859107/Sony-rolls-electric-car-prototype-CES.html</a>"},{"pid":"38b0ced9a1f9a704